<h3><a id="user-content-data-americanexercise" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-americanexercise"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>AmericanExercise</code></h3>
<p>A class defining the exercise period for an American
style option together with any rules governing the
notional amount of the underlying which can be
exercised on any given exercise date and any
associated exercise fees.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>AmericanExercise</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>commencementDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>AdjustableOrRelativeDate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The first day of the exercise period for an American style option.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>earliestExerciseTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) to, and including, the expiration date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>exerciseFeeSchedule</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>ExerciseFeeSchedule</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The fees associated with an exercise date. The fees are conditional on the exercise occurring. The fees can be specified as actual currency amounts or as percentages of the notional amount being exercised.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>expirationDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>AdjustableOrRelativeDate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The last day within an exercise period for an American style option. For a European style option it is the only day within the exercise period.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>expirationTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The latest time for exercise on expirationDate.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>id</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>latestExerciseTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">For a Bermuda or American style option, the latest time on an exercise business day (excluding the expiration date) within the exercise period that notice can be given by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent. Notice of exercise given after this time will be deemed to have been given on the next exercise business day.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>multipleExercise</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>MultipleExercise</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">As defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 12.4. Multiple Exercise, the buyer of the option has the right to exercise all or less than all the unexercised notional amount of the underlying swap on one or more days in the exercise period, but on any such day may not exercise less than the minimum notional amount or more that the maximum notional amount, and if an integral multiple amount is specified, the notional amount exercised must be equal to, or be an integral multiple of, the integral multiple amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>relevantUnderlyingDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>AdjustableOrRelativeDates</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>

<p>A class defining the Bermuda option exercise dates
and the expiration date together with any rules
governing the notional amount of the underlying which
can be exercised on any given exercise date and any
associated exercise fee.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>BermudaExercise</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>bermudaExerciseDates</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>AdjustableOrRelativeDates</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The dates that define the Bermuda option exercise dates and the expiration date. The last specified date is assumed to be the expiration date. The dates can either be specified as a series of explicit dates and associated adjustments or as a series of dates defined relative to another schedule of dates, for example, the calculation period start dates. Where a relative series of dates are defined the first and last possible exercise dates can be separately specified.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>earliestExerciseTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) on each Bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>exerciseFeeSchedule</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>ExerciseFeeSchedule</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The fees associated with an exercise date. The fees are conditional on the exercise occurring. The fees can be specified as actual currency amounts or as percentages of the notional amount being exercised.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>expirationTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The latest time for exercise on expirationDate.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>id</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>latestExerciseTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">For a Bermuda or American style option, the latest time on an exercise business day (excluding the expiration date) within the exercise period that notice can be given by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent. Notice of exercise given after this time will be deemed to have been given on the next exercise business day.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>multipleExercise</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>MultipleExercise</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">As defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 12.4. Multiple Exercise, the buyer of the option has the right to exercise all or less than all the unexercised notional amount of the underlying swap on one or more days in the exercise period, but on any such day may not exercise less than the minimum notional amount or more that the maximum notional amount, and if an integral multiple amount is specified, the notional amount exercised must be equal to, or be an integral multiple of, the integral multiple amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>relevantUnderlyingDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>AdjustableOrRelativeDates</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>

As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.</td>

<td align="left"><code>forecastRate</code></td>

This is a calculated rate determined based on averaging the rates in the rateObservation elements, and incorporates all of the rate treatment and averaging rules. A value of 1% should be represented as 0.01.</td>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-calculationperioddates" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-calculationperioddates"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CalculationPeriodDates</code></h3>
<p>A class for defining the parameters used to generate
the calculation period dates schedule, including the
specification of any initial or final stub
calculation periods. A calculation period schedule
consists of an optional initial stub calculation
period, one or more regular calculation periods and
an optional final stub calculation period. In the
absence of any initial or final stub calculation
periods, the regular part of the calculation period
schedule is assumed to be between the effective date
and the termination date. No implicit stubs are
allowed, i.e. stubs must be explicitly specified
using an appropriate combination of
firstPeriodStartDate, firstRegularPeriodStartDate and
lastRegularPeriodEndDate.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CalculationPeriodDates</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>BusinessDayAdjustments</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The specification of the business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting any calculation period date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business center.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>calculationPeriodFrequency</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>CalculationPeriodFrequency</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The frequency at which calculation period end dates occur with the regular part of the calculation period schedule and their roll date convention.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>effectiveDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>AdjustableOrRelativeDate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The first day of the terms of the trade. This day may be subject to adjustment in accordance with a business day convention.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>firstCompoundingPeriodEndDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Date</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The end date of the initial compounding period when compounding is applicable. It must only be specified when the compoundingMethod element is present and not equal to a value of None. This date may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>firstPeriodStartDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>AdjustableDate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The start date of the calculation period. FpML specifies that for interest rate swaps this date must only be specified if it is not equal to the effective date. It is always specified in the case of equity swaps and credit default swaps with periodic payments. This date may be subject to adjustment in accordance with a business day convention.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>firstRegularPeriodStartDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Date</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The start date of the regular part of the calculation period schedule. It must only be specified if there is an initial stub calculation period. This day may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>id</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>lastRegularPeriodEndDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Date</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The end date of the regular part of the calculation period schedule. It must only be specified if there is a final stub calculation period. This day may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>stubPeriodType</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>StubPeriodTypeEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Method to allocate any irregular period remaining after regular periods have been allocated between the effective and termination date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>terminationDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>AdjustableOrRelativeDate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The last day of the terms of the trade. This date may be subject to adjustments in accordance with the business day convention. It can also be specified in relation to another scheduled date (e.g. the last payment date).</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-calculationperiodfrequency" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-calculationperiodfrequency"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CalculationPeriodFrequency</code></h3>

period end dates occur within the regular part of the
calculation period schedule and their roll date
convention.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CalculationPeriodFrequency</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>

<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>

<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>period</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>PeriodExtendedEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A time period, e.g. a day, week, month, year or term of the stream.</td>
</tr>
<tr>

It is used in conjunction with a frequency and the regular period start date of a calculation period.</td>

If institutions are not specified, it is assumed that reference institutions will be agreed between the parties on the exercise date, or in the case of swap transaction to which mandatory early termination is applicable, the cash settlement valuation date.</td>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-cashsettlementterms" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-cashsettlementterms"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CashSettlementTerms</code></h3>
<p>In FpML, PhysicalSettlementTerms and
CashSettlementTerms extend SettlementTerms. In the
CDM, this extension paradigm has not been used
because SettlementTerms class has been used for
purposes related to securities transactions, while it
is not used as such in the FpML standard (i.e. only
as an abstract construct.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CashSettlementTerms</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>accruedInterest</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Indicates whether accrued interest is included (true) or not (false). For cash settlement this specifies whether quotations should be obtained inclusive or not of accrued interest. For physical settlement this specifies whether the buyer should deliver the obligation with an outstanding principal balance that includes or excludes accrued interest. ISDA 2003 Term: Include/Exclude Accrued Interest.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>cashSettlementAmount</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Money</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The amount paid by the seller to the buyer for cash settlement on the cash settlement date. If not otherwise specified, would typically be calculated as 100 (or the Reference Price) minus the price of the Reference Obligation (all expressed as a percentage) times Floating Rate Payer Calculation Amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>cashSettlementBusinessDays</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Int</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The number of business days used in the determination of the cash settlement payment date. If a cash settlement amount is specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days following the calculation of the final price. If a cash settlement amount is not specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days after all conditions to settlement are satisfied. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dealer</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A dealer from whom quotations are obtained by the calculation agent on the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement. ISDA 2003 Term: Dealer.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>fixedSettlement</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Used for Recovery Lock, to indicate whether fixed Settlement is Applicable or Not Applicable. If Buyer fails to deliver an effective Notice of Physical Settlement on or before the Buyer NOPS Cut-off Date, and if Seller fails to deliver an effective Seller NOPS on or before the Seller NOPS Cut-off Date, then either: (a) if Fixed Settlement is specified in the related Confirmation as not applicable, then the Seller NOPS Cut-off Date shall be the Termination Date; or (b) if Fixed Settlement is specified in the related Confirmation as applicable, then: (i) if the Fixed Settlement Amount is a positive number, Seller shall, subject to Section 3.1 (except for the requirement of satisfaction of the Notice of Physical Settlement Condition to Settlement), pay the Fixed Settlement Amount to Buyer on the Fixed Settlement Payment Date; and (ii) if the Fixed Settlement Amount is a negative number, Buyer shall, subject to Section 3.1 (except for the requirement of satisfaction of the Notice of Physical Settlement Condition to Settlement), pay the absolute value of the Fixed Settlement Amount to Seller on the Fixed Settlement Payment Date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>id</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>minimumQuotationAmout</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Money</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">In the determination of a cash settlement amount, if weighted average quotations are to be obtained, the minimum quotation amount specifies a minimum intended threshold amount of outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specified, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount of the lower of either USD 1,000,000 (or its equivalent in the relevant obligation currency) or the quotation amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Minimum Quotation Amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>quotationAmount</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Money</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">In the determination of a cash settlement amount, if weighted average quotations are to be obtained, the quotation amount specifies an upper limit to the outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specified, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount equal to the floating rate payer calculation amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Quotation Amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>quotationMethod</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>QuotationRateTypeEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The type of price quotations to be requested from dealers when determining the market value of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement. For example, Bid, Offer or Mid-market. ISDA 2003 Term: Quotation Method.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>recoveryFactor</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Decimal</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Used for fixed recovery, specifies the recovery level, determined at contract inception, to be applied on a default. Used to calculate the amount paid by the seller to the buyer for cash settlement on the cash settlement date. Amount calculation is (1 minus the Recovery Factor) multiplied by the Floating Rate Payer Calculation Amount. The currency will be derived from the Floating Rate Payer Calculation Amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>settlementCurrency</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>(</code> <code>FieldWithMeta</code> <code>Text</code> <code>)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The settlement currency is to be specified when the Settlement Amount cannot be known in advance. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>valuationDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>ValuationDate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The number of business days after conditions to settlement have been satisfied when the calculation agent obtains a price quotation on the Reference Obligation for purposes of cash settlement. There may be one or more valuation dates. This is typically specified if the cash settlement amount is not a fixed amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>valuationMethod</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>ValuationMethodEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The ISDA defined methodology for determining the final price of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement. (ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Method). For example, Market, Highest etc.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>valuationTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The time of day in the specified business center when the calculation agent seeks quotations for an amount of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement. ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Time.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-cashtransferbreakdown" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-cashtransferbreakdown"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CashTransferBreakdown</code></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CashTransferBreakdown</code></p>
<table>

<p>A class to specify a cashflow, i.e. the outcome of
either of computation (e.g. interest accrual) or an
assessment of some sort (e.g. a fee). The cashflow
can then be turned into a cash transfer, artefact to
be used as the input to a payment system or the
outcome of it. The associated rosettaKey denotes the
ability to associate a hash value to the Cashflow
instantiations for the purpose of model
cross-referencing, in support of functionality such
as the event effect and the lineage.</p>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-collateral" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-collateral"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>Collateral</code></h3>
<p>A type for defining the obligations of the
counterparty subject to credit support requirements.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>Collateral</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>independentAmount</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>IndependentAmount</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Independent Amount is an amount that usually less creditworthy counterparties are asked to provide. It can either be a fixed amount or a percentage of the Transaction's value. The Independent Amount can be: (i) transferred before any trading between the parties occurs (as a deposit at a third party's account or with the counterparty) or (ii) callable after trading has occurred (typically because a downgrade has occurred). In situation (i), the Independent Amount is not included in the calculation of Exposure, but in situation (ii), it is included in the calculation of Exposure. Thus, for situation (ii), the Independent Amount may be transferred along with any collateral call. Independent Amount is a defined term in the ISDA Credit Support Annex. ('with respect to a party, the amount specified as such for that party in Paragraph 13; if no amount is specified, zero').</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>

or independently from it. It corresponds to the FpML
Trade in the Confirmation view (while the CDM
Execution class corresponds to the FpML trade in the
Pre-Trade view). The associated rosettaKey denotes
the ability to associate a hash value to the Contract
instantiations for the purpose of model
cross-referencing, in support of functionality such
as the event effect and the lineage.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>Contract</code></p>

<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>

<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>CalculationAgent</code></td>

<tr>

<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Date</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">If the trade was cleared (novated) through a central counterparty clearing service, this represents the date the trade was cleared (transferred to the central counterparty).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>closedState</code></td>

<td align="left">Defines the collateral obligations of a party.</td>
</tr>

<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Identifies the form of applicable matrix.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>publicationDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Date</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the publication date of the applicable version of the matrix. When this element is omitted, the ISDA supplemental language for incorporation of the relevant matrix will generally define rules for which version of the matrix is applicable.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-contractualproduct" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-contractualproduct"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>ContractualProduct</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-contractualquantity" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-contractualquantity"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>ContractualQuantity</code></h3>
<p>A class to specify the quantity or notional amount
that is associated with a contractual product and
that is the base for the payout calculation. The
quantity attribute applies to products relating to
securities or tangible assets (such as equities or
commodities), while the notional amount applies to
products pertaining to interest rate, FX or credit
products.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>ContractualQuantity</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>futureValueNotional</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>FutureValueAmount</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The future value notional is specific to BRL CDI swaps, and is specified alongside the notional amount. The value is calculated as follows: Future Value Notional = Notional Amount * (1 + Fixed Rate) ^ (Fixed Rate Day Count Fraction). The currency should always match that expressed in the notional schedule. The value date should match the adjusted termination date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>fxLinkedNotional</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>FxLinkedNotionalSchedule</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The contractual quantity when specified as a notional amount which value is a function of FX parameters.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notionalAdjustments</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>NotionalAdjustmentEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">This attribute specifies the conditions that govern the adjustment to the number of units of the return swap, e.g. execution, portfolio rebalancing. It is typically used in the context of equity swaps.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notionalAmount</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>(</code> <code>ReferenceWithMeta</code> <code>Money</code> <code>)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The contractual quantity when specified as an amount and a currency units without associated schedule or FX terms. When applied to Credit default Swaps, this is the notional amount of protection coverage. ISDA 2003 Term: Floating Rate Payer Calculation Amount.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notionalReset</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">TThe purpose of this indicator is to specify whether the notional reset is applicable (true) or not applicable (false). It is typically used in the context of equity swaps. 2018 ISDA CDM Equity Confirmation for Security Equity Swap: Equity Notional Reset.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notionalSchedule</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>NotionalSchedule</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The contractual quantity when specified as a notional amount with an associated schedule, as used in the case of an amortizing swap where the notional amount decreases over time.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>quantity</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Quantity</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The contractual quantity when specified as an amount/number of securities or tangible assets. The quantity attribute is typical used in the equity and commodity asset classes.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-contractualtermssupplement" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-contractualtermssupplement"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>ContractualTermsSupplement</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-convertiblebond" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-convertiblebond"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>ConvertibleBond</code></h3>

information associated with the contractual product

<h3><a id="user-content-data-creditdefaultpayout" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-creditdefaultpayout"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CreditDefaultPayout</code></h3>
<p>The credit default payout specification provides the
details necessary for determining when a credit
payout will be triggered as well as the parameters
for calculating the payout and the settlement terms.
The associated rosettaKey denotes the ability to
associate a hash value to the CreditDefaultPayout
instantiations for the purpose of model
cross-referencing, in support of functionality such
as the event effect and the lineage.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CreditDefaultPayout</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>cashSettlementTerms</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>[</code> <code>CashSettlementTerms</code> <code>]</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the terms applicable to the cash settlement of a credit event.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>generalTerms</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>GeneralTerms</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The specification of the non-monetary terms for the Credit Derivative Transaction, including the buyer and seller and selected items from the ISDA 2014 Credit Definition article II, such as the reference obligation and related terms.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>id</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>physicalSettlementTerms</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>[</code> <code>PhysicalSettlementTerms</code> <code>]</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the terms applicable to the physical settlement of a credit event.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>protectionTerms</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>[</code> <code>ProtectionTerms</code> <code>]</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the terms for calculating a payout to protect the buyer of the swap in the case of a qualified credit event.  These terms include the notional amount, the applicable credit events, the reference obligation, and in the case of a CDS on mortgage-backed securities, the floatingAmountEvents.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>rosettaKey</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>transactedPrice</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>TransactedPrice</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The qualification of the price at which the contract has been transacted, in terms of market fixed rate, initial points, market price and/or quotation style. In FpML, those attributes are positioned as part of the fee leg.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-crediteventnotice" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-crediteventnotice"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CreditEventNotice</code></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CreditEventNotice</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>businessCenter</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>BusinessCenterEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Inclusion of this business center element implies that Greenwich Mean Time in Section 3.3 of the 2003 ISDA Credit Derivatives Definitions is replaced by the local time of the city indicated by the businessCenter element value.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notifyingParty</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>NotifyingParty</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring. ISDA 2003 Term: Notifying Party.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>publiclyAvailableInformation</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>PubliclyAvailableInformation</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A specified condition to settlement. Publicly available information means information that reasonably confirms any of the facts relevant to determining that a credit event or potential repudiation/moratorium, as applicable, has occurred. The ISDA defined list (2003) is the market standard and is considered comprehensive, and a minimum of two differing public sources must have published the relevant information, to declare a Credit Event. ISDA 2003 Term: Notice of Publicly Available Information Applicable.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-creditevents" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-creditevents"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CreditEvents</code></h3>
<p>A class to specify the applicable Credit Events that
would trigger a settlement, as specified in the
related Confirmation and defined in the ISDA 2014
Credit Definition article IV section 4.1.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CreditEvents</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>bankruptcy</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. The reference entity has been dissolved or has become insolvent. It also covers events that may be a precursor to insolvency such as instigation of bankruptcy or insolvency proceedings. Sovereign trades are not subject to Bankruptcy as 'technically' a Sovereign cannot become bankrupt. ISDA 2003 Term: Bankruptcy.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>creditEventNotice</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>CreditEventNotice</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A specified condition to settlement. An irrevocable written or verbal notice that describes a credit event that has occurred. The notice is sent from the notifying party (either the buyer or the seller) to the counterparty. It provides information relevant to determining that a credit event has occurred. This is typically accompanied by Publicly Available Information. ISDA 2003 Term: Credit Event Notice.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>defaultRequirement</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Money</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">In relation to certain credit events, serves as a threshold for Obligation Acceleration, Obligation Default, Repudiation/Moratorium and Restructuring. Market standard is USD 10,000,000 (JPY 1,000,000,000 for all Japanese Yen trades). This is applied on an aggregate or total basis across all Obligations of the Reference Entity. Used to prevent technical/operational errors from triggering credit events. ISDA 2003 Term: Default Requirement.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>distressedRatingsDowngrade</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. Results from the fact that the rating of the reference obligation is down-graded to a distressed rating level. From a usage standpoint, this credit event is typically not applicable in case of RMBS trades.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>failureToPay</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>FailureToPay</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. This credit event triggers, after the expiration of any applicable grace period, if the reference entity fails to make due payments in an aggregate amount of not less than the payment requirement on one or more obligations (e.g. a missed coupon payment). ISDA 2003 Term: Failure to Pay.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>failureToPayInterest</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. Corresponds to the failure by the Reference Entity to pay an expected interest amount or the payment of an actual interest amount that is less than the expected interest amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Failure to Pay Interest.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>failureToPayPrincipal</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. Corresponds to the failure by the Reference Entity to pay an expected principal amount or the payment of an actual principal amount that is less than the expected principal amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Failure to Pay Principal.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>governmentalIntervention</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. A governmental intervention is an event resulting from an action by a governmental authority that materially impacts the reference entity's obligations, such as an interest rate reduction, principal reduction, deferral of interest or principal, change in priority ranking, or change in currency or composition of payment. ISDA 2014 Term: Governmental Intervention.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>id</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>impliedWritedown</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. Results from the fact that losses occur to the underlying instruments that do not result in reductions of the outstanding principal of the reference obligation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>maturityExtension</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. Results from the fact that the underlier fails to make principal payments as expected.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>obligationAcceleration</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. One or more of the obligations have been declared due and payable before they would otherwise have been due and payable as a result of, or on the basis of, the occurrence of a default, event of default or other similar condition or event other than failure to pay (preferred by the market over Obligation Default, because more definitive and encompasses the definition of Obligation Default - this is more favorable to the Seller). Subject to the default requirement amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Obligation Acceleration.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>obligationDefault</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. One or more of the obligations have become capable of being declared due and payable before they would otherwise have been due and payable as a result of, or on the basis of, the occurrence of a default, event of default or other similar condition or event other than failure to pay. ISDA 2003 Term: Obligation Default.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>repudiationMoratorium</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. The reference entity, or a governmental authority, either refuses to recognise or challenges the validity of one or more obligations of the reference entity, or imposes a moratorium thereby postponing payments on one or more of the obligations of the reference entity. Subject to the default requirement amount. ISDA 2003 Term: Repudiation/Moratorium.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>restructuring</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Restructuring</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. A restructuring is an event that materially impacts the reference entity's obligations, such as an interest rate reduction, principal reduction, deferral of interest or principal, change in priority ranking, or change in currency or composition of payment. ISDA 2003 Term: Restructuring.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>writedown</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A credit event. Results from the fact that the underlier writes down its outstanding principal amount.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-creditlimit" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-creditlimit"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>CreditLimit</code></h3>

As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.</td>

Also, the attribute is of type BusinessCenterTime because of the design decision to only have time that are specified by reference to a timezone, with that class being deemed the proper implementation.</td>

<tr>

<tr>
<td align="left"><code>limitId</code></td>

<p>A class to represent the cash settlement method
defined in the 2006 ISDA Definitions, Section 18.3.
Cash Settlement Methods, paragraph (g) (published in
Supplement number 28).</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>CrossCurrencyMethod</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>cashSettlementCurrency</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>[</code> <code>FieldWithMeta</code> <code>Text</code> <code>]</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The currency, or currencies, in which the cash settlement amount(s) will be calculated and settled. While the order in which the currencies are stated is unimportant, the cash settlement currency or currencies must correspond to one or both of the constituent currencies of the swap transaction. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>cashSettlementReferenceBanks</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>[</code> <code>CashSettlementReferenceBanks</code> <code>]</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A container for a set of institutions that may be called upon to provide rate quotations as part of the method to determine the applicable cash settlement amount. If institutions are not specified, it is assumed that reference institutions will be agreed between the parties on the exercise date, or in the case of swap transaction to which mandatory early termination is applicable, the cash settlement valuation date.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>quotationRateType</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>QuotationRateTypeEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Which rate quote is to be observed, either Bid, Mid, Offer or Exercising Party Pays. The meaning of Exercising Party Pays is defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 17.2. Certain Definitions Relating to Cash Settlement, paragraph (j).</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>

<th align="left">Type/Description</th>

<tbody>
<tr>

<td align="left"><code>FieldWithMeta</code> <code>Text</code></td>

<tr>

<tr>

</tr>
<tr>

Forward points represent the interest rate differential between the two currencies traded and are quoted as a premium or a discount. Forward points are added to, or subtracted from, the spot rate to create the rate of the forward trade.</td>

<tr>

</tr>

<tr>
<td align="left"><code>spotRate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Decimal</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-deliverableobligations" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-deliverableobligations"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DeliverableObligations</code></h3>
<p>A class to specify all the ISDA terms relevant to
defining the deliverable obligations.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>DeliverableObligations</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>acceleratedOrMatured</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. An obligation at time of default is due to mature and due to be repaid, or as a result of downgrade/bankruptcy is due to be repaid as a result of an acceleration clause. ISDA 2003 Term: Accelerated or Matured.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>accruedInterest</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Indicates whether accrued interest is included (true) or not (false). For cash settlement this specifies whether quotations should be obtained inclusive or not of accrued interest. For physical settlement this specifies whether the buyer should deliver the obligation with an outstanding principal balance that includes or excludes accrued interest. ISDA 2003 Term: Include/Exclude Accrued Interest.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>assignableLoan</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>PCDeliverableObligationCharac</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. A loan that is freely assignable to a bank or financial institution without the consent of the Reference Entity or the guarantor, if any, of the loan (or the consent of the applicable borrower if a Reference Entity is guaranteeing the loan) or any agent. ISDA 2003 Term: Assignable Loan.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>category</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>ObligationCategoryEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Used in both obligations and deliverable obligations to represent a class or type of securities which apply. ISDA 2003 Term: Obligation Category/Deliverable Obligation Category.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>consentRequiredLoan</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>PCDeliverableObligationCharac</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. A loan that is capable of being assigned with the consent of the Reference Entity or the guarantor, if any, of the loan or any agent. ISDA 2003 Term: Consent Required Loan.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>directLoanParticipation</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>LoanParticipation</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. A loan with a participation agreement whereby the buyer is capable of creating, or procuring the creation of, a contractual right in favour of the seller that provides the seller with recourse to the participation seller for a specified share in any payments due under the relevant loan which are received by the participation seller. ISDA 2003 Term: Direct Loan Participation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>excluded</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A free format string to specify any excluded obligations or deliverable obligations, as the case may be, of the reference entity or excluded types of obligations or deliverable obligations. ISDA 2003 Term: Excluded Obligations/Excluded Deliverable Obligations.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>fullFaithAndCreditObLiability</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published additional provisions for U.S. Municipal as Reference Entity. ISDA 2003 Term: Full Faith and Credit Obligation Liability.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>generalFundObligationLiability</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published additional provisions for U.S. Municipal as Reference Entity. ISDA 2003 Term: General Fund Obligation Liability.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>indirectLoanParticipation</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>LoanParticipation</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">ISDA 1999 Term: Indirect Loan Participation. NOTE: Only applicable as a deliverable obligation under ISDA Credit 1999.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>listed</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Indicates whether or not the obligation is quoted, listed or ordinarily purchased and sold on an exchange. ISDA 2003 Term: Listed.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>maximumMaturity</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Period</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. An obligation that has a remaining maturity from the Physical Settlement Date of not greater than the period specified. ISDA 2003 Term: Maximum Maturity.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notBearer</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. Any obligation that is not a bearer instrument. This applies to Bonds only and is meant to avoid tax, fraud and security/delivery provisions that can potentially be associated with Bearer Bonds. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Bearer.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notContingent</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. In essence Not Contingent means the repayment of principal cannot be dependant on a formula/index, i.e. to prevent the risk of being delivered an instrument that may never pay any element of principal, and to ensure that the obligation is interest bearing (on a regular schedule). ISDA 2003 Term: Not Contingent.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notDomesticCurrency</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>NotDomesticCurrency</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Any obligation that is payable in any currency other than the domestic currency. Domestic currency is either the currency so specified or, if no currency is specified, the currency of (a) the reference entity, if the reference entity is a sovereign, or (b) the jurisdiction in which the relevant reference entity is organised, if the reference entity is not a sovereign. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Domestic Currency.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notDomesticIssuance</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Any obligation other than an obligation that was intended to be offered for sale primarily in the domestic market of the relevant Reference Entity. This specifies that the obligation must be an internationally recognised bond. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Domestic Issuance.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notDomesticLaw</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. If the reference entity is a Sovereign, this means any obligation that is not subject to the laws of the reference entity. If the reference entity is not a sovereign, this means any obligation that is not subject to the laws of the jurisdiction of the reference entity. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Domestic Law.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notSovereignLender</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Any obligation that is not primarily (majority) owed to a Sovereign or Supranational Organisation. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Sovereign Lender.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>notSubordinated</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. An obligation that ranks at least equal with the most senior Reference Obligation in priority of payment or, if no Reference Obligation is specified in the related Confirmation, the obligations of the Reference Entity that are senior. ISDA 2003 Term: Not Subordinated.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>othReferenceEntityObligations</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">This element is used to specify any other obligations of a reference entity in both obligations and deliverable obligations. The obligations can be specified free-form. ISDA 2003 Term: Other Obligations of a Reference Entity.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>revenueObligationLiability</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. Defined in the ISDA published additional provisions for U.S. Municipal as Reference Entity. ISDA 2003 Term: Revenue Obligation Liability.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>specifiedCurrency</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>SpecifiedCurrency</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">An obligation and deliverable obligation characteristic. The currency or currencies in which an obligation or deliverable obligation must be payable. ISDA 2003 Term: Specified Currency.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>transferable</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">A deliverable obligation characteristic. An obligation that is transferable to institutional investors without any contractual, statutory or regulatory restrictions. ISDA 2003 Term: Transferable.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-determinationmethod" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-determinationmethod"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DeterminationMethod</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-discountingmethod" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-discountingmethod"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DiscountingMethod</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-disputeresolution" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-disputeresolution"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DisputeResolution</code></h3>
<p>A class to specify the election terms under which a
party disputes (i) the Calculation Agent’s
calculation of a Delivery Amount or a Return Amount,
or (ii) the Value of any Transfer of Eligible Credit
Support or Posted Credit Support. Parties can specify
such election either through a business center time
or through a custom election. ISDA 2016 Credit
Support Annex for Initial Margin, paragraph 13,
General Principles, (g): Dispute Resolution.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>DisputeResolution</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>otherTerms</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Text</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The custom Resolution Time election that might be specified by the parties.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>resolutionTime</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>BusinessCenterTime</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The time by which the dispute needs to be resolved, failure of which would trigger a recalculation alongside a process that is specified as part of the agreement. ISDA 2016 Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin, paragraph 13, General Principles, (g)(i): Resolution Time.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividendcurrency" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividendcurrency"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendCurrency</code></h3>
<p>A class to specify the currency in which the
dividends will be denominated, i.e. either in the
dividend currency or in a currency specified as part
of the contract.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>DividendCurrency</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>currency</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>(</code> <code>FieldWithMeta</code> <code>Text</code> <code>)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">The currency in which the dividend is denominated. The list of valid currencies is not presently positioned as an enumeration as part of the CDM because that scope is limited to the values specified by ISDA and FpML. As a result, implementers have to make reference to the relevant standard, such as the ISO 4217 standard for currency codes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>

</tr>
<tr>

</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the method according to which the dividend is determined, e.g. the dividend currency.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividenddatereference" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividenddatereference"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendDateReference</code></h3>

<tr>
<td align="left"><code>paymentDateOffset</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Offset</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>

</tr>

</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividendpaymentdate" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividendpaymentdate"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendPaymentDate</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividendpayout" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividendpayout"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendPayout</code></h3>
<p>A class describing the dividend payout ratio
associated with an equity underlier. In certain cases
the actual ratio is not known on trade inception, and
only general conditions are then specified.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>DividendPayout</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>

<td align="left"><code>Decimal</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the total actual dividend payout ratio associated with the equity underlier. A ratio of 90% should be expressed at 0.90.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendPayoutRatioCash</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Decimal</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the cash actual dividend payout ratio associated with the equity underlier. A ratio of 90% should be expressed at 0.90.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendPayoutRatioNonCash</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Decimal</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the non cash actual dividend payout ratio associated with the equity underlier. A ratio of 90% should be expressed at 0.90.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividendreturnterms" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividendreturnterms"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendReturnTerms</code></h3>
<p>A class describing the conditions governing the
payment of dividends to the receiver of the equity
return, with the exception of the dividend payout
ratio, which is defined for each of the underlying
components.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>DividendReturnTerms</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th align="left">Field</th>
<th align="left">Type/Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendAmountType</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>DividendAmountTypeEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies whether the dividend is paid with respect to the Dividend Period.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendCurrency</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>DividendCurrency</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the currency in which the dividend will be denominated, e.g. the dividend currency, or a specified currency. This class is not specified as such in FpML, which makes use of the CurrencyAndDeterminationMethod.model to specify such terms.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendEntitlement</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>DividendEntitlementEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Defines the date on which the receiver of the equity return is entitled to the dividend.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendPaymentDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>DividendPaymentDate</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies when the dividend will be paid to the receiver of the equity return. Has the meaning as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions. Is not applicable in the case of a dividend reinvestment election.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendPayout</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>DividendPayout</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Specifies the dividend payout ratio associated with the underlier. In FpML 5.10 the payout is positioned at the underlier level, although there is an intent to reconsider this approach and position it at the leg level. This is approach adopted by the CDM.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendPeriod</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>DividendPeriodEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions: Dividend Period as either the First Period or the Second Period.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendPeriodEffectiveDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>(</code> <code>BasicReferenceWithMeta</code> <code>Date</code> <code>)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions: Dividend Period as such other period determined as provided in the related Confirmation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendPeriodEndDate</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>(</code> <code>BasicReferenceWithMeta</code> <code>Date</code> <code>)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions: Dividend Period as such other period determined as provided in the related Confirmation.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>dividendReinvestment</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>Bool</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Boolean element that defines whether the dividend will be reinvested or not.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>excessDividendAmount</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>DividendAmountTypeEnum</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Determination of Gross Cash Dividend per Share.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"><code>extraordinaryDividendsParty</code></td>
<td align="left"><code>Optional</code> <code>(</code> <code>ReferenceWithMeta</code> <code>Party</code> <code>)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left"></td>
<td align="left">Reference to the party which determines if dividends are extraordinary in relation to normal levels.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-documentation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-documentation"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>Documentation</code></h3>
