<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividendamounttypeenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividendamounttypeenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendAmountTypeEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify whether the dividend
is paid with respect to the Dividend Period.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>DividendAmountTypeEnum_AsSpecifiedInMasterConfirmation</code>
The Amount is determined as provided in the relevant
Master Confirmation.</li>
<li><code>DividendAmountTypeEnum_ExAmount</code>
The ex-date for a dividend occurs during a dividend
period.</li>
<li><code>DividendAmountTypeEnum_PaidAmount</code>
The payment date for a dividend occurs during a
dividend period.</li>
<li><code>DividendAmountTypeEnum_RecordAmount</code>
The record date for a dividend occurs during a
dividend period.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividenddatereferenceenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividenddatereferenceenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendDateReferenceEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the date by
reference to which the dividend will be paid.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_AdHocDate</code>
The dividend date will be specified ad-hoc by the
parties, typically on the dividend ex-date.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_CashSettlePaymentDateExDiv</code>
If 'Dividend Payment Date(s)' is specified in
the Transaction Supplement as 'Cash Settlement
Payment Date – Ex Dividend'', then the
Dividend Payment Date in respect of a Dividend Amount
shall be the Cash Settlement Payment Date relating to
the end of the Dividend Period during which the
Shares commenced trading 'ex' the relevant
dividend on the Exchange.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_CashSettlePaymentDateIssuerPayment</code>
If 'Dividend Payment Date(s)' is specified in
the Transaction Supplement as 'Cash Settlement
Payment Date – Issuer Payment', then the Dividend
Payment Date in respect of a Dividend Amount shall be
the Cash Settlement Payment Date relating to the end
of the Dividend Period during which the issuer pays
the relevant dividend to a holder of record provided
that in the case where the Equity Amount Payer is the
party specified to be the sole Hedging Party and the
Hedging Party has not received the Dividend Amount by
such date, then the date falling a number of Currency
Business Days as specified in the Cash Settlement
Payment Date after actual receipt by the Hedging
Party of the Received Ex Amount or Paid Ex Amount (as
applicable).</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_CashSettlementPaymentDate</code>
If 'Dividend Payment Date(s)' is specified in
the Transaction Supplement as 'Cash Settlement
Payment Date', then the Dividend Payment Date in
respect of a Dividend Amount shall be the Cash
Settlement Payment Date relating to the end of the
Dividend Period during which the Shares commenced
trading 'ex' the relevant dividend on the
Exchange.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_CumulativeEquityExDiv</code>
Total of dividends which go ex, paid on next
following Cash Settlement Payment Date, which is
immediately following the Dividend Period during
which the Shares commence trading ex-dividend on the
Exchange.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_CumulativeEquityPaid</code>
Total of paid dividends, paid on next following Cash
Settlement Payment Date, which is immediately
following the Dividend Period during which the
dividend is paid by the Issuer to the holders of
record of a Share.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_CumulativeLiborExDiv</code>
Total of dividends which go ex, paid on next
following Payment Date, which is immediately
following the Dividend Period during which the Shares
commence trading ex-dividend on the Exchange, or
where the date on which the Shares commence trading
ex-dividend is a Payment Date, such Payment Date.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_CumulativeLiborPaid</code>
Total of paid dividends, paid on next following
Payment Date, which is immediately following the
Dividend Period during which the dividend is paid by
the Issuer to the holders of record of a Share.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_DividendPaymentDate</code>
Date on which the dividend will be paid by the
issuer.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_DividendValuationDate</code>
In respect of each Dividend Period, the relevant
Dividend Valuation Date.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_EquityPaymentDate</code>
Equity payment date of the swap.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_ExDate</code>
Date on which a holder of the security is entitled to
the dividend.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_FloatingAmountPaymentDate</code>
If 'Dividend Payment Date(s)' is specified in
the Transaction Supplement as 'Floating Amount
Payment Date', then the Dividend Payment Date in
respect of a Dividend Amount shall be the first
Payment Date falling at least one Settlement Cycle
after the date that the Shares have commenced trading
'ex' the relevant dividend on the Exchange.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_FollowingPaymentDate</code>
The next payment date of the swap.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_RecordDate</code>
Date on which the dividend will be recorded in the
books of the paying agent.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_SharePayment</code>
If 'Dividend Payment Date(s)' is specified in
the Transaction Supplement as 'Share
Payment', then the Dividend Payment Date in
respect of a Dividend Amount shall fall on a date on
or before the date that is two (or any other number
that is specified in the Transaction Supplement)
Currency Business Days following the day on which the
Issuer of the Shares pays the relevant dividend to
holders of record of the Shares.</li>
<li><code>DividendDateReferenceEnum_TerminationDate</code>
Termination date of the swap.</li>
</ul>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-dividendperiodenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-dividendperiodenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>DividendPeriodEnum</code></h3>
<p>2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions: First
Period, Second Period |</p>
<ul>
<li><code>DividendPeriodEnum_FirstPeriod</code>
2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions: First
Period means each period from, and including, one
Cash Settlement Payment Date or Settlement Date, as
the case may be, to, but excluding, the next
following Cash Settlement Payment Date or Settlement
Date, as the case may be, except that (i) the initial
Dividend Period will commence on, and include, the
Clearance System Business Day that is one Settlement
Cycle following the Trade Date and (ii) the final
Dividend Period will end on, but exclude, the final
Cash Settlement Payment Date or Settlement Date, as
the case may be.</li>
<li><code>DividendPeriodEnum_SecondPeriod</code>
2002 ISDA Equity Derivatives Definitions: Second
Period means each period from, but excluding, one
Valuation Date to, and including, the next Valuation
Date, except that (i) the initial Dividend Period
will commence on, but exclude, the Trade Date and
(ii) the final Dividend Period will end on, and
include, the final Valuation Date or, in respect of a
Physically-settled Forward Transaction to which
Variable Obligation is not applicable, the date that
is one Settlement Cycle prior to the Settlement Date.</li>
</ul>

<p>The enumeration values to qualify the time stamps
that can be associated with a lifecycle event.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_clearingConfirmationDateTime</code>
The date and time on which trade was confirmed as
cleared.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_clearingDateTime</code>
The date and time on the trade was cleared.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_clearingSubmissionDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the event was submitted
for clearing.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_eventCreationDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the event was created.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_eventExpirationDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the event will be
considered expired.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_eventProcessingDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the event was processed.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_eventSentDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the event was sent.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_eventSubmittedDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the event was submitted.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_executionDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the trade execution was
performed.</li>
<li><code>EventTimeStampQualificationEnum_transactionCreationDateTime</code>
The date and time on which the transaction has been
created. This timestamp is specified as such by the
CME ClearPort Matched IRS Trade submission API
specification: 'The transaction date time of the
trade. Represents the date &amp; time on which the
trade was initially generated either by CME Clearing
or firm. The transaction date time may be assigned by
CME Clearing at the point the trade is reported as
cleared. Transaction date time can also be provided
by an external submitter of the trade at the point
the trade is submitted.'</li>
</ul>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-optiontypeenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-optiontypeenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>OptionTypeEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the type of the
option. In FpML, OptionTypeEnum is a union with
PutCallEnum, which specifies whether the option is a
put or a call.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>OptionTypeEnum_Call</code>
A call option gives the holder the right to buy the
underlying asset by a certain date for a certain
price.</li>
<li><code>OptionTypeEnum_Payer</code>
A 'payer' option: If you buy a
'payer' option you have the right but not the
obligation to enter into the underlying swap
transaction as the 'fixed' rate/price payer
and receive float.</li>
<li><code>OptionTypeEnum_Put</code>
A put option gives the holder the right to sell the
underlying asset by a certain date for a certain
price.</li>
<li><code>OptionTypeEnum_Receiver</code>
A 'receiver' option: If you buy a
'receiver' option you have the right but not
the obligation to enter into the underlying swap
transaction as the 'fixed' rate/price
receiver and pay float.</li>
<li><code>OptionTypeEnum_Straddle</code>
A straddle strategy, which involves the simultaneous
buying of a put and a call of the same underlier, at
the same strike and same expiration date</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-originatingeventenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-originatingeventenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>OriginatingEventEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumeration values to specify the originating
event that gave way to the trade.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_Allocation</code>
The trade results from an allocation event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_Amendment</code>
The trade results from a trade amendment.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_Clearing</code>
The trade results from a clearing event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_Compression</code>
The trade results from a compression event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_Exercise</code>
The trade results from an exercise event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_NewTrade</code>
The trade results from a new trade event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_Novation</code>
The trade presented results from a novation event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_PartialExercise</code>
The trade results from a partial exercise event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_PartialNovation</code>
The trade results from a partial novation event.</li>
<li><code>OriginatingEventEnum_Transfer</code>
The trade results from a transfer.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-packagetypeenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-packagetypeenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PackageTypeEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the type of package
transaction.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_Butterfly</code>
A strategy in which a firm either pays or receives
fixed for intermediate term (the 'body'), and
does the opposite (receives or pays fixed) for a
short and a long term (the 'wings'').</li>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_CalendarRoll</code>
A strategy in which a swap is used to Roll from one
IMM date into another IMM swap.</li>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_CalendarSpread</code>
A strategy in which 2 trades on different dates are
done at the same time, e.g., Sept vs June.</li>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_Custom</code>
A package created for a particular client need e.g.
portfolioCompression, termination.</li>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_IndexRoll</code>
A strategy in which a firms buys new version of index
and sells and old version of the same index.</li>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_OneCancelsOthers</code>
A package in which only a maximum of one of the
components will be executed (used for credit limit
checking/orders).</li>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_SwapSpread</code>
A strategy in which a firm either buys a treasury and
enters a payer swap, or sells treasury and enters a
receiver swap.</li>
<li><code>PackageTypeEnum_Switch</code>
A strategy in which a firm either pays or receives
fixed for some term versus the opposite (receives or
pays fixed) for different term. Typically the second
term starts at the completion of the first.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-partyidsourceenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-partyidsourceenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PartyIdSourceEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumeration values associated with party
identifier sources.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_ARNU</code>
Alien Registration Number, number assigned by a
social security agency to identify a non-resident
person.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_BIC</code>
The Bank Identifier Code.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_CCPT</code>
Passport Number, number assigned by an authority to
identify the passport number of a person.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_CUST</code>
Customer Identification Number, number assigned by an
issuer to identify a customer.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_DRLC</code>
Drivers License Number, number assigned by an
authority to identify a driver's license.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_EMPL</code>
Employee Identification Number, number assigned by a
registration authority to an employee.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_LEI</code>
The ISO 17442:2012 Legal Entity Identifier.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_NIDN</code>
National Identity Number, number assigned by an
authority to identify the national identity number of
a person..</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_SOSE</code>
Social Security Number, number assigned by an
authority to identify the social security number of a
person.</li>
<li><code>PartyIdSourceEnum_TXID</code>
Tax Identification Number, number assigned by a tax
authority to identify a person.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-partyroleenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-partyroleenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PartyRoleEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values for the party role. The
enumerated values go beyond the FpML partyRoleScheme
as they also include elements that are part of the
FpML Trade, such as the Barrier Determination Agent
and the Hedging Party.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Accountant</code>
Organization responsible for preparing the accounting
for the trade.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_AllocationAgent</code>
The organization responsible for supplying the
allocations for a trade to be allocated to multiple
accounts/organizations.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ArrangingBroker</code>
The organization that arranged the trade, i.e.
brought together the counterparties.
Synonyms/Alternatives: Inter-dealer broker, agent.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_BarrierDeterminationAgent</code>
The party specified in the related confirmation as
Barrier Determination Agent.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Beneficiary</code>
Organization that suffers the economic benefit of the
trade.  The beneficiary may be distinct from the
principal/counterparty - an example occurs when a
hedge fund trades via a prime broker; in this case
the principal is the prime broker, but the
beneficiary is the hedge fund.  This can be
represented as a payer/receiver account in the name
of the hedge fund, but it is also possible to add the
party role of 'Beneficiary' at the
partyTradeInformation level.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_BookingParty</code>
The entity for which the organization supporting the
trade's processing  has booked/recorded the
trade. This is used in non-reporting workflows
situations in which the trade doesn't need to be
reported but a firm still wants to specify their own
side.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Buyer</code>
Acquirer of the legal title to the financial
instrument. In the case of an option, the buyer is
the holder of the option. In the case of a swap or
forward, the buyer will be determined by industry
best practice.  This does not refer to an investor or
investment manager or other organization on what is
typically called  the 'Buy side'; for that,
see the 'Client' role. Corresponds to
'Buyer' as defined in certain regulations
such as ESMA MiFID II/MIFIR RTS 22 field 9.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_BuyerDecisionMaker</code>
The party or person who, having legal authority to
act on behalf of the trade counterparty acting as
Buyer as defined in this coding scheme, made the
decision to acquire the financial instrument.
Corresponds to 'buyer decision maker' as
defined in ESMA's MIFIR RTS 23 report. This does
not refer to the decision maker for what is
traditionally called the 'Buy side'; for
that, see the 'Client Decision Maker' role.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Chargor</code>
The party that provides credit support under English
Law.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ClearingClient</code>
An organization that clears trades through a clearing
house, via a clearing broker (member of the clearing
house) who acts as an agent on its behalf. The term
'client' refers to the organization's
role in the clearing process in relation to its
clearing broker, and not whether it is a price maker
or taker in the execution process.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ClearingExceptionParty</code>
A party to the trade that claims a clearing
exception, such as an end-user exception under
Dodd-Frank Act provisions.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ClearingFirm</code>
Organization that submits the trade to a clearing
house on behalf of the principal.
Synonyms/alternates:  Futures Commission Merchant
(FCM), Clearing Broker, Clearing Member Firm. Some
implementations use 'Clearing Broker' as
synonym.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ClearingOrganization</code>
The organization that acts as a central counterparty
to clear a derivatives contract.  This is used to
represent the role of Central Counterparties (CCPs)
or Derivative Clearing Organizations (DCOs).
Sometimes called 'ClearingService'. Some
implementations also use the term 'Clearer'.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Client</code>
Client as defined under ESMA MIFIR. This is generally
the investor or other client of an investment firm,
and is synonymous with the Beneficiary in many
circumstances.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ClientDecisionMaker</code>
The party or person who, having legal authority to
act on behalf of a trade counterparty, made the
decision to acquire or sell the financial instrument.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ConfirmationPlatform</code>
Organization serving as a financial intermediary for
the purposes of electronic confirmation or providing
services for post-processing of transactional data.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ContractualParty</code>
A party to a contractual document.  If the intended
usage relates to the context of the trade lifecycle,
more specific annotations have been defined which
might be more appropriate.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_CounterPartyAffiliate</code>
Organization officially attached to the counterparty.
e.g. partner, branch, subsidiary.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_CounterPartyUltimateParent</code>
The topmost entity or organization, within the
corporate hierarchy, responsible for the reporting
party.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Counterparty</code>
An economic counterparty to the trade. Synonym:
principal.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_CreditSupportProvider</code>
Organization that enhances the credit of another
organization (similar to guarantor, but may not fully
guarantee the obligation).</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Custodian</code>
Organization that maintains custody of the asset
represented by the trade on behalf of the
owner/principal.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_DataSubmitter</code>
Entity submitting the transaction report to the
competent authority.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_DeterminingParty</code>
The party referenced is specified in the contract
confirmation as Determination Party.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_DisputingParty</code>
Organization that is disputing the trade or
transaction.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_DocumentRepository</code>
A marketplace organization which purpose is to
maintain document records.  If the intended usage
relates to the context of the trade lifecycle, more
specific annotations have been defined which might be
more appropriate.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ExecutingBroker</code>
The (generally sell-side) organization that executed
the trade; the price-making party.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ExecutingEntity</code>
Entity executing the transaction.  If the transaction
is executed directly by the reporting party, it will
be the reporting party.  If it is executed by an
execution agent or an affiliated party on behalf of
the reporting party, it will be that affiliate or
agent.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ExecutionAgent</code>
The (generally buy-side) organization that acts to
execute trades on behalf of an investor. Typically
this is an investment manager or asset manager, and
also makes the investment decisions for the investor.
If required, a separate InvestmentDecision role can
be specified to distinguish that the party making the
investment decision is different.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ExecutionFacility</code>
The facility, exchange, or market where the trade was
executed. Synonym: Swap Execution Facility,
Designated Contract Market, Execution Venue.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Guarantor</code>
Organization that backs (guarantees) the credit risk
of the trade.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_HedgingParty</code>
The ISDA Hedging Party that is specified in the
related confirmation as Hedging, or if no Hedging
Party is specified, either party to the contract.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_OrderTransmitter</code>
The entity transmitting the order to the reporting
firm. Synonym: Transmitting Firm.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Pledgor</code>
The party that provides credit support under New York
Law.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_PrimeBroker</code>
The organization that takes on or took on the credit
risk for this trade by stepping in between the two
economic parties (without a central counterparty
clearing mechanism).</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_PriorTradeRepository</code>
The trade repository at which the trade was reported
previous to the current trade repository.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_PublicationVenue</code>
The reporting service (whether trade repository,
market data service, or exchange/facility/venue data
distribution service) that published the report of
this trade.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ReportingParty</code>
The party with the regulatory responsibility to
report this trade.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ReportingPartyAffiliate</code>
Organization officially attached to the reporting
party  e.g. partner, branch, subsidiary.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_ReportingPartyUltimateParent</code>
The topmost entity or organization, within the
corporate hierarchy, responsible for the reporting
party.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_SecuredParty</code>
The party that receives credit support under New York
or English Law.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_Seller</code>
A counterparty in a trade, which performs in one of
the following capacities: 1) it transfers or agrees
to transfer in the future an instrument or title to
that instrument in exchange for payment, 2) it writes
a derivatives instrument such as an option or a swap
in which it provides risk protection to the buyer.
This does not refer to the broker/dealer or other
organization on what is typically called  the
'Sell side'; for that, see the 'Executing
Broker' role. Corresponds to 'Seller' as
defined in certain regulations such as ESMA MiFID
II/MIFIR RTS 22 field 16.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_SellerDecisionMaker</code>
The party or person who, having legal authority to
act on behalf of the trade counterparty acting as
Seller as defined in this coding scheme, made the
decision to sell the financial instrument.
Corresponds to 'seller decision maker' as
defined in ESMA's MIFIR RTS 23 report. This does
not refer to the decision maker for what is
traditionally called the 'Sell side'; for
that, see the 'Trader' person role.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_SettlementAgent</code>
The organization that makes or receives payments on
behalf of the given principal party.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_TradeRepository</code>
An organization that maintains records of the trade
for regulatory reporting purposes.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_TradeSource</code>
The organization that originally supplied the record
of the trade. In the context of regulatory reporting,
it is the submitter of the trade record to a
regulator or TR.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_TradingManager</code>
The entity responsible for managing the
assets/investments of this party.  Synonnym:  Asset
Manager, Investment Manager, Trading Advisory.</li>
<li><code>PartyRoleEnum_TradingPartner</code>
An entity with which this party trades from time to
time, ie. with which it acts as a counterparty on
some transactions.   This role is used for static
reference data, not individual transactions.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-payrelativetoenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-payrelativetoenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PayRelativeToEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify whether payments
occur relative to the calculation period start date
or end date, each reset date, valuation date or the
last pricing date.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>PayRelativeToEnum_CalculationPeriodEndDate</code>
Payments will occur relative to the last day of each
calculation period.</li>
<li><code>PayRelativeToEnum_CalculationPeriodStartDate</code>
Payments will occur relative to the first day of each
calculation period.</li>
<li><code>PayRelativeToEnum_LastPricingDate</code>
Payments will occur relative to the last Pricing Date
of each Calculation Period.</li>
<li><code>PayRelativeToEnum_ResetDate</code>
Payments will occur relative to the reset date.</li>
<li><code>PayRelativeToEnum_ValuationDate</code>
Payments will occur relative to the valuation date.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-payerreceiverenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-payerreceiverenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PayerReceiverEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify an interest rate
stream payer or receiver party.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>PayerReceiverEnum_Payer</code>
The party identified as the stream payer.</li>
<li><code>PayerReceiverEnum_Receiver</code>
The party identified as the stream receiver.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-paymentstatusenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-paymentstatusenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PaymentStatusEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumeration values to specify the payment status.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>PaymentStatusEnum_Disputed</code>
The payment is disputed.</li>
<li><code>PaymentStatusEnum_Instructed</code>
The payment has been instructed.</li>
<li><code>PaymentStatusEnum_Pending</code>
The payment is pending instruction.</li>
<li><code>PaymentStatusEnum_Settled</code>
The payment has been settled.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-paymenttypeenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-paymenttypeenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PaymentTypeEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumeration values to specify the type of
payment.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_AmendmentFee</code>
A cash flow associated with an amendment lifecycle
event.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_AssignmentFee</code>
A cash flow resulting from the assignment of a
contract to a new counterparty.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_BrokerageCommission</code>
The brokerage commission.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_Coupon</code>
A cash flow corresponding to the periodic accrued
interests.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_CreditEvent</code>
A cashflow resulting from a credit event.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_DividendReturn</code>
A cash flow corresponding to the synthetic dividend
of an equity underlier asset traded through a
derivative instrument.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_ExerciseFee</code>
A cash flow associated with an exercise lifecycle
event.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_Fee</code>
A generic term for describing a non-scheduled
cashflow that can be associated either with the
initial contract, with some later corrections to it
(e.g. a correction to the day count fraction that has
a cashflow impact) or with some lifecycle events.
Fees that are specifically associated with
termination and partial termination, increase,
amendment, and exercise events are qualified
accordingly.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_IncreaseFee</code>
A cash flow associated with an increase lifecycle
event.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_Interest</code>
Interest, without qualification as to whether it a
gross or net interest relates cashflow.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_InterestReturn</code>
A cash flow corresponding to the return of the
interest rate portion of a derivative instrument that
has different types of underlying assets, such as a
total return swap.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_NetCashflow</code></li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_NetInterest</code>
Net interest across payout components. Applicable to
products such as interest rate swaps.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_NovationFee</code>
The novation fee.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_PartialTerminationFee</code>
A cash flow associated with a partial termination
lifecycle event.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_Premium</code>
The premium associated with an OTC contract such as
an option or a cap/floor.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_PriceReturn</code>
A cash flow corresponding to the return of the price
portion of a derivative instrument that has different
types of underlying assets, such as a total return
swap.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_PrincipalExchange</code>
A cash flow which amount typically corresponds to the
notional of the contract and that is exchanged
between the parties on trade inception and reverted
back when the contract is terminated.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_TerminationFee</code>
A cash flow associated with a termination lifecycle
event.</li>
<li><code>PaymentTypeEnum_UpfrontFee</code>
An upfront cashflow associated to the swap to adjust
for a difference between the swap price and the
current market price.</li>
</ul>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-periodextendedenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-periodextendedenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PeriodExtendedEnum</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-priceexpressionenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-priceexpressionenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>PriceExpressionEnum</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-productidsourceenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-productidsourceenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>ProductIdSourceEnum</code></h3>

<li><code>ProductIdSourceEnum_FIGI</code>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-quantifierenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-quantifierenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>QuantifierEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify a logical
quantification, i.e. either All or Any.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>QuantifierEnum_All</code>
The condition in the scope of the quantifier is true
of every member of the domain i.e. every one of the
elements in scope.</li>
<li><code>QuantifierEnum_Any</code>
The condition in the scope of the quantifier is true

</ul>

<p>The enumerated values to specify the type of
quotation rate to be obtained from each cash
settlement reference bank.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>QuotationRateTypeEnum_Ask</code>
An ask rate.</li>
<li><code>QuotationRateTypeEnum_Bid</code>
A bid rate.</li>
<li><code>QuotationRateTypeEnum_ExercisingPartyPays</code>
If optional early termination is applicable to a swap
transaction, the rate, which may be a bid or ask
rate, which would result, if seller is in-the-money,
in the higher absolute value of the cash settlement
amount, or, is seller is out-of-the-money, in the
lower absolute value of the cash settlement amount.</li>
<li><code>QuotationRateTypeEnum_Mid</code>
A mid-market rate.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-quotationsideenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-quotationsideenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>QuotationSideEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the side from which
perspective a value is quoted.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>QuotationSideEnum_Ask</code>
A value 'asked' by a seller for an asset,
i.e. the value at which a seller is willing to sell.</li>
<li><code>QuotationSideEnum_Bid</code>
A value 'bid' by a buyer for an asset, i.e.
the value a buyer is willing to pay.</li>
<li><code>QuotationSideEnum_Mid</code>
A value midway between the bid and the ask value.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-quotationstyleenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-quotationstyleenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>QuotationStyleEnum</code></h3>

When quotation style is 'Price', the

<h3><a id="user-content-data-ratetreatmentenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-ratetreatmentenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>RateTreatmentEnum</code></h3>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-regulatoryregimeenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-regulatoryregimeenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the regulatory
regimes. The ISDA 2018 CSA is used as one input to
qualify those enumerated values. The display name
corresponds to the set of values specified as part of
of the ISDA 2016 and 2018 CSA for Initial Margin.
2016 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin:
Regime | 2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial
Margin: Regime.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_AustraliaMarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Australian
Prudential Standard CPS 226 Margining and risk
mitigation for non-centrally cleared derivatives.</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_CFTC_MarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Margin requirements
adopted by the U.S. Commodity Futures Trading
Commission pursuant to CEA § 4s(e).</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_CanadaMarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Guideline E-22,
Margin Requirements for Non-Centrally Cleared
Derivatives issued by the Canadian Office of the
Superintendent of Financial Institutions</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_EMIR_MarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Regulation (EU) No
648/2012 of the European Parliament and of the
Council of 4 July 2012 on OTC derivatives, central
counterparties and trade repositories (including the
EMIR RTS).</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_HongKongMarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Chapter CR-G-14
'Non-centrally Cleared OTC Derivatives
Transactions – Margin and Other Risk Mitigation
Standards' in the Banking Supervisory Policy
Manual issued by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority.</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_JapanMarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Margin rules
adopted by the Financial Services Agency of Japan
pursuant to Article 40, Item 2 of the Financial
Instruments and Exchange Act (kin’yuu shouhin
torihiki hou) (Act No. 25 of 1948) and by the
Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries and
the Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry pursuant
to the Commodity Derivatives Act (shouhin sakimono
torihiki hou) (Act No. 239 of 1950) (including their
subordinated regulations and the related supervisory
guidelines).</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_SEC_MarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Margin requirements
adopted by the U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission pursuant to Exchange Act § 15F(e).</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_SingaporeMarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Guidelines on
Margin Requirements for Non-centrally Cleared OTC
Derivatives Contracts issued by the Monetary
Authority of Singapore (MAS) pursuant to section 321
of the Securities and Futures Act, Chapter 289 of
Singapore.</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_SwitzerlandMarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Margin rules
adopted by the Swiss Federal Council pursuant to
Article 110-111 of the Financial Market
Infrastructure Act as well as Articles 100 to 107 and
Annexes 3 to 5 of the Financial Market Infrastructure
Ordinance.</li>
<li><code>RegulatoryRegimeEnum_US_PrudentialMarginRules</code>
2018 ISDA Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin,
paragraph 13, General Principles: Margin requirements
adopted by a 'prudential regulator' (as
defined in CEA § 1a(39)) pursuant to CEA § 4s(e) and
Exchange Act § 15F(e).</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-resetrelativetoenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-resetrelativetoenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>ResetRelativeToEnum</code></h3>

relative to the first or last day of a calculation
period.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>ResetRelativeToEnum_CalculationPeriodEndDate</code>

calculation period.</li>
<li><code>ResetRelativeToEnum_CalculationPeriodStartDate</code>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-resourcetypeenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-resourcetypeenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>ResourceTypeEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the type of a
resource (e.g. document).</p>
<ul>

Document describing the legal terms of a transaction.</li>
<li><code>ResourceTypeEnum_SupplementalMaterialEconomicTerms</code>
Document providing supplemental material economic
terms to the FpML data representation.  The initial
intended usage is to fulfill the CFTC Part 45 rule

<h3><a id="user-content-data-rollconventionenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-rollconventionenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>RollConventionEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the period term as
part of a periodic schedule, i.e. the calculation
period end date within the regular part of the
calculation period. The value could be a rule, e.g.
IMM Settlement Dates, which is the 3rd Wednesday of
the month, or it could be a specific day of the
month, such as the first day of the applicable month.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_EOM</code>
Rolls on month end dates irrespective of the length
of the month and the previous roll day.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_FRI</code>
Rolling weekly on a Friday</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_FRN</code>
Roll days are determined according to the FRN
Convention or Euro-dollar Convention as described in
ISDA 2000 definitions.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_IMM</code>
IMM Settlement Dates. The third Wednesday of the
(delivery) month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_IMMAUD</code>
The last trading day of the Sydney Futures Exchange
90 Day Bank Accepted Bills Futures contract (see
<a href="http://www.sfe.com.au/content/sfe/trading/con_specs.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.sfe.com.au/content/sfe/trading/con_specs.pdf</a>).
One Sydney business day preceding the second Friday
of the relevant settlement.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_IMMCAD</code>
The last trading day/expiration day of the Canadian
Derivatives Exchange (Bourse de Montreal Inc)
Three-month Canadian Bankers' Acceptance Futures
(Ticker Symbol BAX). The second London banking day
prior to the third Wednesday of the contract month.
If the determined day is a Bourse or bank holiday in
Montreal or Toronto, the last trading day shall be
the previous bank business day. Per Canadian
Derivatives Exchange BAX contract specification.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_IMMNZD</code>
The last trading day of the Sydney Futures Exchange
NZ 90 Day Bank Bill Futures contract (see
<a href="http://www.sfe.com.au/content/sfe/trading/con_specs.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.sfe.com.au/content/sfe/trading/con_specs.pdf</a>).
The first Wednesday after the ninth day of the
relevant settlement month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_MON</code>
Rolling weekly on a Monday.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_NONE</code>
The roll convention is not required. For example, in
the case of a daily calculation frequency.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_SAT</code>
Rolling weekly on a Saturday</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_SFE</code>
Sydney Futures Exchange 90-Day Bank Accepted Bill
Futures Settlement Dates. The second Friday of the
(delivery) month</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_SUN</code>
Rolling weekly on a Sunday</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_TBILL</code>
13-week and 26-week U.S. Treasury Bill Auction Dates.
Each Monday except for U.S. (New York) holidays when
it will occur on a Tuesday.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_THU</code>
Rolling weekly on a Thursday</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_TUE</code>
Rolling weekly on a Tuesday</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum_WED</code>
Rolling weekly on a Wednesday</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__1</code>
Rolls on the 1st day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__10</code>
Rolls on the 10th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__11</code>
Rolls on the 11th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__12</code>
Rolls on the 12th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__13</code>
Rolls on the 13th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__14</code>
Rolls on the 14th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__15</code>
Rolls on the 15th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__16</code>
Rolls on the 16th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__17</code>
Rolls on the 17th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__18</code>

<li><code>RollConventionEnum__19</code>
Rolls on the 19th day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__2</code>
Rolls on the 2nd day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__20</code>

<li><code>RollConventionEnum__22</code>
Rolls on the 22nd day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__23</code>
Rolls on the 23rd day of the month.</li>
<li><code>RollConventionEnum__24</code>

<li><code>RollConventionEnum__25</code>

<li><code>RollConventionEnum__26</code>

Rolls on the 27th day of the month.</li>

<h3><a id="user-content-data-roundingdirectionenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-roundingdirectionenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>RoundingDirectionEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the rounding
direction and precision to be used in the rounding of
a rate.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>RoundingDirectionEnum_Down</code>
A fractional number will be rounded down to the
specified number of decimal places (the precision).
For example, 5.29 and 5.25 rounded down to 1 decimal
place are 5.2 and 5.2 respectively.</li>
<li><code>RoundingDirectionEnum_Nearest</code>
A fractional number will be rounded either up or down
to the specified number of decimal places (the
precision) depending on its value. For example, 5.24
would be rounded down to 5.2 and 5.25 would be
rounded up to 5.3 if a precision of 1 decimal place
were specified.</li>
<li><code>RoundingDirectionEnum_Up</code>
A fractional number will be rounded up to the
specified number of decimal places (the precision).
For example, 5.21 and 5.25 rounded up to 1 decimal
place are 5.3 and 5.3 respectively.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-sensitivitiesenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-sensitivitiesenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>SensitivitiesEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the methodology
according to which sensitivities to equity indices,
funds and ETFs on hand, and commodity indices on the
other hand, are computed for the purpose of the ISDA
2016 and 2016 CSA for Initial Margin. ISDA 2016
Credit Support Annex for Initial Margin, paragraph
13, General Principles, (gg).</p>
<ul>
<li><code>SensitivitiesEnum_Alternative</code>
The parties agree that in respect of the relevant
sensitivities, the delta is allocated back to
individual constituents.</li>
<li><code>SensitivitiesEnum_NotSpecified</code>
The methodology to compute relevant sensitivities is
not specified.</li>
<li><code>SensitivitiesEnum_Standard</code>
The relevant sensitivities are addressed by the
standard preferred approach where the entire delta is
put into the applicable asset class/category.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-settledentitymatrixsourceenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-settledentitymatrixsourceenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>SettledEntityMatrixSourceEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the relevant settled
entity matrix source.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>SettledEntityMatrixSourceEnum_ConfirmationAnnex</code>
The Relevant Settled Entity Matrix shall be the list
agreed for this purpose by the parties. The list is
not included as part of the electronic confirmation.</li>
<li><code>SettledEntityMatrixSourceEnum_NotApplicable</code>
The term is not applicable.</li>
<li><code>SettledEntityMatrixSourceEnum_Publisher</code>
The Settled Entity Matrix published by the Index
Publisher.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a id="user-content-data-settlementrateoptionenum" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#data-settlementrateoptionenum"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>data</code> <code>SettlementRateOptionEnum</code></h3>
<p>The enumerated values to specify the settlement rate
options as specified in the Annex A to the 1998 FX
and Currency Options Definitions.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_ARS_BNAR_ARS01</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
Argentine Peso/U.S. Dollar Specified Rate, expressed
as the amount of Argentine Pesos per one U.S. Dollar,
for settlement on the same day (or, if such day is
not a Business Day in New York, for settlement on the
first succeeding day that is a Business Day in both
Buenos Aires and New York) which appears on the
Reuters Screen BNAR Page at the close of business in
Buenos Aires on that Rate Calculation Date.</li>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_ARS_EMTA_INDICATIVE_SURVEY_RATE_ARS04</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
Argentine Peso/U.S. Dollar Specified Rate for U.S.
Dollars, expressed as the amount of Argentine Pesos
per one U.S. Dollar, for settlement on the same day,
as published on EMTA's web site (<a href="http://www.emta.org" rel="nofollow">www.emta.org</a>) at
approximately 1:00 p.m. (Buenos Aires time), or as
soon thereafter as practicable, on such Rate
Calculation Date. The Spot Rate shall be calculated
by EMTA (or a service provider EMTA may select in its
sole discretion) pursuant to the EMTA ARS Indicative
Survey Methodology (which means a methodology, dated
as of January 2, 2003, as amended from time to time,
for a centralized industry-wide survey of financial
institutions that are active participants in the
Argentine Peso/U.S. Dollar markets for the purpose of
determining the EMTA ARS Indicative Survey Rate).</li>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_ARS_EMTA_INDUSTRY_SURVEY_RATE_ARS03</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
Argentine Peso/U.S. Dollar Specified Rate for U.S.
Dollars, expressed as the amount of Argentine Pesos
per one U.S. Dollar, for settlement on the same day,
as published on EMTA's web site (<a href="http://www.emta.org" rel="nofollow">www.emta.org</a>) at
approximately 1:00 p.m. (Buenos Aires time), or as
soon thereafter as practicable, on such Rate
Calculation Date. The Spot Rate shall be calculated
by EMTA (or a service provider EMTA may select in its
sole discretion) pursuant to the EMTA ARS Industry
Survey Methodology (which means a methodology, dated
as of January 2, 2003, as amended from time to time,
for a centralized industry-wide survey of financial
institutions in Buenos Aires that are active
participants in the Argentine Peso/U.S. Dollar spot
markets for the purpose of determining the EMTA ARS
Industry Survey Rate).</li>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_ARS_MAE_ARS05</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
volume weighted average Argentine Peso/U.S. Dollar
Rate of all trades executed in the electronic market
for a Rate Calculation Day expressed as the amount of
Argentine Pesos per one U.S. Dollar, for settlement
on the same day, reported by the Mercado Abierto
Electronico (the 'MAE') at approximately 3:00
pm, Buenos Aires time, and published on the FOREX-MAE
Page as the 'PPN' rate ('Promedio
Ponderado Noticiado') on <a href="http://www.mae.com.ar" rel="nofollow">www.mae.com.ar</a> on that
Rate Calculation Date.</li>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_ARS_OFFICIAL_RATE_ARS02</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
Argentine Peso/U.S. Dollar offered rate for U.S.
Dollars, expressed as the amount of Argentine Pesos
per one U.S. Dollar, for settlement on the same day
quoted by Banco de la Nacion (in accordance with the
Convertibility Law of March 27, 1991 and Regulatory
Decree No. 529/91 of April 1, 1991, as may be amended
from time to time) for that Rate Calculation Date.</li>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_BRL_BRBY_BRL01</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
Brazilian Real/U.S. Dollar Specified Rate, expressed
as the amount of Brazilian Reais per one U.S. Dollar,
for settlement in two Business Days (where such days
are Business Days in both Sao Paulo and New York)
which appears on the Reuters Screen BRBY Page under
the caption 'INTBK FLTING (LAST)' at
approximately 11:00 a.m., Sao Paulo time, on that
Rate Calculation Date.</li>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_BRL_EMTA_INDICATIVE_SURVEY_RATE_BRL13</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
Brazilian Real/U.S. Dollar Specified Rate for U.S.
Dollars, expressed as the amount of Brazilian Reais
per one U.S. Dollar, for settlement in two Business
Days, as published on EMTA's web site
(<a href="http://www.emta.org" rel="nofollow">www.emta.org</a>) at approximately 12:00 p.m. (Sao Paulo
time), or as soon thereafter as practicable, on such
Rate Calculation Date. The Spot Rate shall be
calculated by EMTA (or a service provider EMTA may

<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_CURRENCY_IMPLIED_RATE__ADR__CURA1</code>
the Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the
Reference Currency/U.S. Dollar exchange rate,
expressed as the amount of Reference Currency per one
U.S. Dollar, determined on the basis of quotations
provided by Reference Dealers on that Rate
Calculation Date of that day's price of a
Specified Company's American Depositary Receipt
or American Depositary Receipts (the 'ADR' or
'ADRs', as appropriate) and the price of the
local share or shares of such Specified Company of
the same type and in the same quantity represented by
such ADR or ADRs, as the case may be (the
'Share' or 'Shares', as appropriate).
The Calculation Agent will request each of the
Reference Dealers to provide a firm quotation of (A)
in the case where one ADR represents less than one
Share, its bid and offer price (in the Reference
Currency) for one Share and its bid and offer price
(in U.S. Dollars) for the number of ADRs which
represent such Share and (B) in all other cases, its
bid andoffer price (in the Reference Currency) for
the Share or Shares, as the case may be, and its bid
and offer price (in U.S. Dollars) for one ADR. If one
or more quotations are provided, the rate for a Rate
Calculation Date will equal the ratio of (1) the
arithmetic mean of the midpoint of the bid and offer
prices quoted in the Reference Currency by each
Reference Dealer for such Share or Shares, as the
case may be, and (2) the arithmetic mean of the
midpoint of the bid and offer prices quoted in U.S.
Dollars by each Reference Dealer for such ADR or
ADRs, as the case may be, subject to an adjustment,
if any, by the Calculation Agent to reduce the effect
of momentary disparities in the prices of the Share
or Shares and the ADR or ADRs, as appropriate. The
quotations used to determine the Spot Rate for a Rate
Calculation Date will be determined in each case at
the Specified Time on the Rate Calculation Date or,
if no such time is specified, the time chosen by
theCalculation Agent.</li>
<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_CURRENCY_IMPLIED_RATE__LOCAL_ASSET__CURA2</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be the

of Local Assets whose face value equals the Specified
Amount. If one or more quotations are provided, the

of (A) the arithmetic mean of the midpoint of the bid
and offer prices quoted in the Reference Currency by
each Reference Dealer for such Local Assets and (B)
the arithmetic mean of the midpoint of the bid and
offer prices quoted in the Settlement Currency by
each Reference Dealer for suchLocal Assets. The

<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_CURRENCY_MUTUAL_AGREEMENT_CURA3</code>

<li><code>SettlementRateOptionEnum_CURRENCY_REFERENCE_DEALERS_CURA4</code>
The Spot Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be
determined on the basis of quotations provided by
Reference Dealers on that Rate Calculation Date of
that day's Specified Rate, expressed as the
amount of Reference Currency per one unit of
Settlement Currency, for settlement on the Settlement
Date. The Calculation Agent will request the
Specified Office of each of the Reference Dealers to
provide a firm quotation of its Specified Rate for a
transaction where the amount of Reference Currency
equals the Specified Amount. If four quotations are
provided, the rate for a Rate Calculation Date will
be the arithmetic mean of the Specified Rates,
without regard to the Specified Rates having the
highest and lowest value. If exactly three quotations
are provided, the rate for a Rate Calculation Date
will be the Specified Rate provided by the Reference
Dealer that remains after disregarding the Specified
Rates having the highest and lowest values. For this
purpose, ifmore than one quotation has the same
highest value or lowest value, then the Specified
Rate of one of such quotations shall be disregarded.
If exactly two quotations are provided, the rate for
a Rate Calculation Date will be the arithmetic mean
of the Specified Rates. If only one quotation is
provided, the rate for a Rate Calculation Date will
be the Specified Rate quoted by that Reference
Dealer. The quotations used to determine the Spot
Rate for a Rate Calculation Date will be determined
in each case at the Specified Time on that Rate
Calculation Date or, if no such time is specified,
the time chosen by the Calculation Agent.</li>
